			<td class="section_post" valign="top" height="120">
				Meant to put my 2c in last week but forgot. I'll probably give this two more eps, but I'm 80% going<br />
to drop it. Just too many cheesy cliches for me to take it as serious as they want to present it.<br />
While I can accept &quot;The Blackout&quot; at face value, they fail to explain the other mysterious things<br />
they just take for granted. Such as why combustion engines don't work when fire and guns do. Then<br />
what about steam? I mean the ol' US ol A did span the continent without electricity at one time, and<br />
while it probably wouldn't have survived wholly in the wake... There would probably be a significant<br />
remnant, and at the vary least a better semblance of older civilization at 15 post event... Although<br />
none of that touches on what would have happened to the nuclear reactors and if the blackout<br />
affected those some how to prevent meltdowns...  nukepills.com/nuclear-reactor-maps.htm<br />
<br />
In the end, they are just trying to do too much. The incessantly interconnected ensemble is annoying<br />
too, but I guess expected from a Network budget/production. If you're looking for a good post apoc<br />
show, try Falling Skies, Survivors(BBC), or Jeremiah, over this. I put this in the same let down<br />
basket as Terra Nova. 			</td>
